Jordan Brooks has been offered an international music scholarship and needs to travel to the UK to accept it. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The COVID-19 pandemic and lockdown struggles are not stopping a young Cape Town violinist from following his dreams. Jordan Brooks has been offered an international music scholarship and needs to travel to the UK to accept it. So he’s hoping to raise the funds he needs by performing a virtual concert this weekend. READ: Madonna post blocked by Instagram for false virus video Brooks is only 16-years old but already he is a musical talent to be reckoned with. When he was 13, he was appointed the youngest-ever concert master of the Cape Town Philharmonic Youth Orchestra. Last year, he won the National Youth Music Competition and now, the young violinist is a proud scholarship holder for the prestigious Chetham’s School of Music in Manchester, in the UK. The scholarship opportunity came quickly and unexpectedly in the midst of lockdown. READ: Hugh Masekela scholarship launched Leaving Jordan with little time to financially prepare. So his friends in the industry have stepped in to host a fundraising concert. The virtual concert takes place on 9 August. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.